```julia
function clean_column(col)
    return replace(strip(lowercase(col)), r"\s+" => "_")
end
```
This function takes a single argument `col`, which is the column name to be cleaned. It first converts the string to lowercase using `lowercase`. Then, it strips any leading or trailing whitespaces using `strip`. Finally, it replaces any spaces and hyphens with an underscore using `replace(r"\s+" => "_")`. The resulting string is returned as the cleaned column name.
